        "body":  "Codex review: NEEDS_CORRECTION\n\nFinding: live menu-handoff prose still describes only File + Edit + Play after this PR adds View. The code registers and paints the View menu, but the current-state rustdoc/comment surface is not fully widened:\n\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:354` says the FIFO drains commands enqueued by the File + Edit + Play menu bars.\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:390` says the registry resolves \"all three points\".\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs:635` and `:801` still say File + Edit + Play menu bars enqueue/push onto the handoff.\n- `crates/editor-egui-host/src/handoff.rs:76-77` still says commands are pushed when a File, Edit, or Play item is activated.\n\nThese are live source docs/comments, not dated history. Since A4 adds View and already updates adjacent menu prose, leaving these narrow claims repeats the stale-prose sweep issue from #297 and makes the menu-command surface internally inconsistent. Please widen them to File + Edit + Play + View / all four points and include `handoff.rs` in the sweep.\r\n",
